        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Top 5 Classes by Number of Ligands\n\n| Rank | Ligand Class | Ligand Count | % of Total |\n|------|-------------|-------------|------------|\n| 1 | Ligands not selected | 1,339 | 23.3% |\n| 2 | Amino Acids | 297 | 5.2% |\n| 3 | Aliphatic amines | 250 | 4.4% |\n| 4 | Pyridines (azines) | 248 | 4.3% |\n| 5 | Carboxylic acids | 182 | 3.2% |\n\n> **Note:** The largest category, \"Ligands not selected,\" is a catch-all for ligands that haven't been assigned to a specific chemical class. If we exclude that bin, the **top 5 named classes** are **Amino Acids** (297), **Aliphatic amines** (250), **Pyridines/azines** (248), **Carboxylic acids** (182), and **Aza-macrocycles** (165).",
