      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Chemistry Insight\n\nThe dominance of amino acids and aliphatic amines reflects the historical importance of biologically relevant ligands in coordination chemistry — amino acids are ubiquitous metal binders in biological systems, while simple amines serve as fundamental N-donor ligands. Pyridine derivatives rank highly because the aromatic nitrogen is an excellent σ-donor, making pyridines workhorses in both analytical and industrial coordination chemistry.\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46 (Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes)*",
